Date: 2000-06-21

Title: Infrared singularities in the renormalization group flow of Yang-Mills

theories in the axial gaugeAuthors: Annamaria Panza and Roberto Soldati (U. of Bologna)

Comments: 12 pages, 3 figures, revised version to appear in Phys. Lett. B

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B493 (2000) 197-208

It is shown, by explicit calculation in the axial gauge, that therenormalization group flow for the Wilson loop in perturbation theory doesexhibit singularities and consequently it can not eventually reproduce thegauge invariant result, when the infrared cut off is removed